This paper deals with the control of robotic systems, specifically autonomous aerial vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a method that combines model predictive control (MPC) with reinforcement learning, which involves training a deep neural network policy, indicating that it could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sensors and obstacle avoidance, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively.
